			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>On the contrary, bloodshed is the <em>result</em> of high transaction costs, not an input into those costs. People fight when they can&#8217;t bargain to the efficient solution, and here the efficient solution involves a coalition that is powerful enough to certainly win a fight.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

